data.title: Elton Brand, Basketball Player
data.meta_description: Elton Brand stats and bio. Stats averages season by season. Quick access to game by game stats.
data.text:
Elton Brand - Points

Elton Brand scores a career high 44 points (2006)

On February 10, 2006, Elton Brand tied his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 44 points in LA Clippers's home win against Memphis, 91-87. He also had 9 rebounds, 2 assists, 2 steals and 2 blocks. He shot 17/26 from two, shooting at 65.4% from the field. He also shot 10/10 from the free-throw line.

Elton Brand - Rebounds

Elton Brand grabs a career high 23 rebounds (2002)

On February 25, 2002, Elton Brand tied his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 23 rebounds in LA Clippers's road win against Memphis, 77-90. He also had 27 points, 1 steal and 2 blocks.

Elton Brand - Assists

Elton Brand gives a career high 10 assists (2003)

On January 26, 2003, Elton Brand set his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 10 assists in LA Clippers's road loss against Indiana, 108-101. He also had 17 points, 14 rebounds, 2 steals and 1 block.

Elton Brand - Steals

Elton Brand has a career high 5 steals (2006)

On February 21, 2006, Elton Brand tied his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 5 steals in LA Clippers's road loss against Dallas, 93-91. He also had 20 points, 8 rebounds and 4 assists.

Elton Brand - Blocks

Elton Brand blocks a career high 8 shots (2003)

On October 30, 2003, Elton Brand tied his career high in blocks in a NBA game. That day he went for 8 blocks in LA Clippers's road loss against Seattle, 109-100. He also had 21 points, 15 rebounds and 5 assists.
